<item>
            <title>[SOLR-595] support field level boosting to morelikethis handler.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-595</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Allow boosting to be specified for particular fields when using more like this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Parse out &quot;mlt.qf parameters&quot; to get boosts in dismax like format (existing code from DisMax param parse code used to produce a Map&amp;lt;String,Float&amp;gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Iterate through mltquery terms, get boost by looking at field from which mltquery term came,  and multiply boost specified in map by existing term boost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If mlt.boost=false, then you get the same boost values as in map/mlt.qf parameters,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If mlt.boost=true then you get normalized boost multiplied by specified boost (which makes sense to me).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
